<span id="freeTextContainer1070622012498041865">What this slim volume lacks in pages it makes up in power &amp; beautiful, careful writing. There is not a word wasted. In one case, too much so as I found the introduction of their son into the story quite jarring.<br/><br/>I originally thought that husband Yukitomo was as much a victim of late 19th century customs as the unfortunate women who he controls, but now I think he was just a self centred, not very bright jerk, who never realised what a treasure he had in his wife, Tomo.<br/><br/>I&apos;ve thought about what I kn</span>
  <span id="freeText1070622012498041865" style="display:none">What this slim volume lacks in pages it makes up in power &amp; beautiful, careful writing. There is not a word wasted. In one case, too much so as I found the introduction of their son into the story quite jarring.<br><br>I originally thought that husband Yukitomo was as much a victim of late 19th century customs as the unfortunate women who he controls, but now I think he was just a self centred, not very bright jerk, who never realised what a treasure he had in his wife, Tomo.<br><br>I've thought about what I know about Japanese customs &amp; the importance of saving face &amp; now realise <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Tomo's final actions are a gentle revenge. &amp; Yukitomo knew that all right!<br><br>The books final lines;<br><br><i> His body suffered the full force of emotions that his wife had struggled to suppress for forty years past. The shock was enough to split his arrogant ego in two. </i><br><br>Go Tomo! <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br><br>Many of the female characters play battledore &amp; shuttlecock (an early form of badminton) My whole family used to play badminton. I love Japanese art. Good enough reason for a picture!<br><br><blockquote>
