        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer90835707" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11788612216995033652">Rather depresive and very sad, but strong and very beautiful. Fom first issue in 1957 remains till today very popular novel in Japan. From female author.<br/>Historical novel (from end of 19. century) mainly about two heroines. Tomo is beautiful young woman from poor but noble (samurai) family, wife of wealthy and succesful young and handsome Japanese nobleman (samurai, but of much better origin than her) whom she loves and who married her in her age of 14. Now she is 30 and she has two children, old</span>
  <span id="freeText11788612216995033652" style="display:none">Rather depresive and very sad, but strong and very beautiful. Fom first issue in 1957 remains till today very popular novel in Japan. From female author.<br />Historical novel (from end of 19. century) mainly about two heroines. Tomo is beautiful young woman from poor but noble (samurai) family, wife of wealthy and succesful young and handsome Japanese nobleman (samurai, but of much better origin than her) whom she loves and who married her in her age of 14. Now she is 30 and she has two children, older son, his heir, and beloved little girl. She seems to be very happy. But he doesn´t loves her anymore and he asks her to secretly find for him young virgin as his concubine. She is desperate but she was raised in "old school" -´Husband will is law for his (samurai) wife´. And she still loves him and they have two childern... Also she finds Suga, 15 years old, innocent and sweet girl from good (not noble, merchant´s origin)but poor family with many debts. She would be sold as prostitute and statute of concubine is better for her, but she doesn´t know nothing about it, only that ´she must serve to certain nobleman because honor a prosperity of her family´. And Tomo takes Suga with her a and swears to herself that she would always defend Suga and take care for her. Poor Suga, horrified but still obedient, must later sleep with her master. Tomo suffers on jealousy toward Suga, but feels pitty toward her, too. And Suga beginns to love her master and suffers jealousy and hateres toward Tomo, but feels pitty for her, too. Wife and concumine unde one roof, they both suffers very much. But this is not all: when is Suga 18 and not little girl anymore, the nobleman takes in family another girl (16 years old, but very small and fragile, she looks as child) from samurai poor family, rapes her and takes her as another concubine(and he pays a huge sum of money her family for it -money was law in these times and poor female victim was gladly sold by her relatives). But she is not too obedient and she saves herself later because it - she is married by her master to his neffe, poor young noble, and she has her own happy family. But Tomo and Suga still suffers in husband/master house. Than the nobleman seduces Miya, bride of his son (which was secretly platonic lesbian love of sad abandoned and unsatisfied Tomo, too - she forbids herself strictly from love to another man, because she has husband, but some woman would be not such case, not her infidelity toward her husband :o)). He falls in lifetime love with Miya and remains in it till her death (but he still sleeps with Suga, too), while (alone) Tomo terrible fears that her son finds it... She suffers till her death in old age and on her deathbed she does her first attemt to defy her husband which angries him very much.<br />Very cruel but impresive image of old noble (samurai) Japanese family in end of 19. century.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11788612216995033652" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
